<br>
The only difference between Islam and the rest of the religions of Abraham is that it is a bit more honest, more forthright, about its extremist portions. The Torah and the Bible both have scriptures that order the faithful to whack other people, they are just bound up a little less than clearly due to translations and allegory. Islam just goes out and says it in the clear.<br>
<br>
The problem is not Islam per se, it is that Islam has not experienced a Reformation style event. Christianity was rough, and I mean ROUGH, back before Reformation. Martin Luther and his wacky bunch helped to change all that. The Muslims could really use a sweeping reform of the faith to bring it in line with a changed and changing world. <br>
<br>
C'mon, it's a Dark Ages religion. They were all rough back then. We just grew out of that stage.<br>
<br>
As to the Canadian military being skilled, equipped, etc, I said nothing about the soldiers, nor would I. My father served 24 years in the US Army and I have great respect for any professional soldier. Hell, Canadian snipers were in Afghanistan and even our SF guys said they were the best they'd seen. Still, Canada doesn't go out of its' way to lavish budget on the Canadian military. The necessary skill level required of their individual trooper reflects a lack of personnel resources, not a better military. They are forced to do more with less, and Canadian work ethic is up to that task. <p>a_Bearhat01<br>
